Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.80,0:01:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a Tenpai{I really hope it's tenpai though it sounds rather like just "tenpa"} already!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.34,0:01:58.81,Song,,0,0,0,,Tenpai{テンパイ} = 2 "sevens" aligned; effectively the same as Riichi Eyes or Scissors{why the fuck they needed so much different names for one rather simple thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.58,0:02:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.88,0:02:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Imbecile! Shouldn't have been pressing it! \NYou can't press properly even with "{[Riichi] }Eyes{I hope he means riichi eyes and not something like "you're blind to push"}" in front of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.28,0:02:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.55,0:02:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In a tag match{I hope it's "match" and not some other "machi"}, you have to follow the partner you teamed up with into all the ups and downs{no clue what else is this "uunfuun" thing but onomatopeia for oscillation}.{maybe it's "your partner has his rises and falls"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.61,0:02:23.45,Song,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fade(900,900)\c&HFFFFFF&\bord0\shad3\blur0.7\4c&H6738C5&\b1\fnHitch Hike\fs65\pos(310,80)\3c&HC898A1&}Episode 17\N {\fs80}\N\N\N\NPerson on my Mind
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.16,0:02:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you’re adroit yourself{/have the abilities}, \Nyou can't exert any power on them{/affect this outcome}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's Tenpai for the other side!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.94,0:02:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The right one can be slippery...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.62,0:02:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it one tempo{thankfully this is clearly not tenpai} faster than the others{added, lit is just "one beat quicker?"}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.87,0:02:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.42,0:02:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.36,0:02:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.42,0:02:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Showing off how lucky I'm feeling today!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.33,0:02:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't that one was a good omen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was one tempo faster, \Nyet you aligned it nicely anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.20,0:03:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're starting to make some allowances{/leeway} \Nin the way you press the buttons.{/Looks like you're getting pretty comfortable with the way you're hitting.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.57,0:03:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't afford to lose in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.91,0:03:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,After Oumi did so much for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I will hand in the resignation from Slothium.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did Oumi do this, all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.42,0:03:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse yourself losing in such a place,\Na dream of challenging Daiba Ryo will remain a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight with everything on the line!\NThrow your everything at me, unrestrained!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oumi went to such measures just to help me fight Daiba. \NWhere did this come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Move aside! \NIt's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.13,0:04:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you lose, you still stay in Knights. \NBut my ass will get kicked from Generals!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.58,0:04:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm nowhere near losing yet...{/It's not decided yet that I lost}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.62,0:04:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut the fuck up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.68,0:04:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't win for toffee with that way of pressing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.82,0:04:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, nice! \NThat's a nice omen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.00,0:04:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The prime reason for bands break-up \Nis members becoming bad buddies{/quarreling}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.22,0:04:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The two that cannot concert their opinions \Ncan never play a good concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.57,0:04:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Long story short, the other guys \Nain't having a good game today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.37,0:04:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's time to swap here as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.48,0:04:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Daiba, I'm winning for certain here, \Nwhatever it takes to fight you sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.34,0:05:01.31,Song,,0,0,0,,Akiyama Chika
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Akiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.74,0:05:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The memory of that time you had to give up,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.08,0:05:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to abandon your dream of becoming an athlete \Nbecause of that injury right before the tournament,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,even to this day, \Nit pains my heart vividly{/actively/truly} with remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.19,0:05:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A more prodigious athlete than anyone else, \Nand also with a huge love for rhythmic gymnastics -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.20,0:05:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the only such person I know, \Ntherefore I ask you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no doubt \Nthat you would make a magnificent coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.34,0:05:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm aware that for the time being you're working hard to qualify for an instructor already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.34,0:05:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, please give it a good thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.11,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to trouble you with my personal affairs, \Nbut I'm getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:06:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet wishing for the gymnastics club of our alma-mater{I hope it's boukou and not boku wo} to thrive and prosper, I'm writing this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Akiyama is getting married...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.59,0:06:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A gymnastics coach in my alma-mater?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The practices were always grueling, \Nbut that still was a really fun time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.39,0:06:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Remaining time: 3 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, we can win even making some allowance{I dunno why but he uses same words as daiba before}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.01,0:06:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I can only do that much to catch up! \NShit! It was all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.99,0:06:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Game is concluded. Winner team - \NKen Hayashi & Otonashi Ginya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Be noted, the next General-Knight castling{/interchange} match
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,will be held between today's two winners.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.84,0:06:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, we are enemies from now on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.94,0:07:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord4}Nothing personal, but I'll be the one basking in the spotlight in the next match. It's not your turn{ [to be promoted] (I hope)} yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Be sure to live up to that conviction next time we meet.{no clue, lit: I'll start entirely in accordance to those words}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.68,0:07:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go further and smash \Nthat self-confidence with my stick!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.76,0:07:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't disappoint me, will ya?{I look forward to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.12,0:07:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.10,0:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No child's play!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.30,0:07:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said - \NI want you to hit me with everything you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.21,0:07:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight at earnest!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't possibly know it{this construction is usually used as "I can't know if" but here it makes no sense}, but Oumi entrusted to me \Nfighting you for him as well, Daiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We both challenge you now.{added}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.31,0:07:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing away my current job as an instructor \Nis a hard choice to make,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.96,0:07:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,yet it's tempting to see amazing players \Nbrought up by my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach Kamoi{her surname, \N鴨井ゆり}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.38,0:08:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be nice \Nto push the youth towards their dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.71,0:08:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, if I tell them I'm returning to suburbs{countryside}, \Nmom and dad would surely be delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.35,0:08:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dream.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginya...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.93,0:08:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Still 4 o'clock? Though it's a little early, maybe \NI'll stop by a parlor for an interview on my way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.77,0:08:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginya, you feel like joining me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.01,0:08:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I had plans for{/'m busy} today. \NThough once I'm done with this, I'm free tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.31,0:08:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can it be because of a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.15,0:08:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.65,0:08:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever. \NWork hard, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.07,0:08:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a no way to go. \NYou should ask her out every once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.26,0:08:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls abhor it when you neglect them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.23,0:09:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you were perfectly aware of it after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.36,0:09:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want me to persuade him to change his mind, \NI will have to refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.01,0:09:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.17,0:09:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I know trying to persuade Daiba \Nis a nonstarter at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the matter{ you wanted to discuss} then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.26,0:09:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to allow me \Nto attend{witness} Daiba's match{es?}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.64,0:09:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,His match?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.21,0:09:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's nothing else I can do as a doctor, \NI will at least do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.68,0:09:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to see to it \Nthat Daiba carries on fighting till the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Slothium rules do not allow other players...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.22,0:09:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My withdrawal{it's explicitly not a resignation} notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.86,0:09:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Please accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.90,0:09:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I implore you, \NI know you can arrange that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.44,0:09:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Was delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.85,0:09:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:09:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, at 6{ oclock}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.49,0:10:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting, in front of station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Today at 6?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.27,0:10:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so sudden, \NI'm already busy for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.97,0:10:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to tell you something important. \NWe absolutely should talk it over today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.31,0:10:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have some errands to run today, \NI can wait until you're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At what hour you think you can do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming the match starts at 5 and lasts for 2 hours,\NI guess, it's around 7 that I can leave from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.59,0:10:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I may get bogged down somewhere on the way, \Nso let's make it something like 8 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. Then, make sure to show up at 8 today \Nunder the clock in front of station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.80,0:10:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.84,0:10:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what is it so important \Nshe wants to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.61,0:11:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't afford worrying about Yuri now. \NUntil the match is over, I have to focus entirely on the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For today's match, a new machine \Nof Slothium's original design, Goldracer, would be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.94,0:11:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This machine comes \Nwith a new service function called Gold Time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.88,0:11:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,New machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.05,0:11:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if you can navigate that machine \Nto the multiplier the usual way.{words are clear but meaning is oblique}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.05,0:11:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems 150 000 multiplier combinations \Nare available on it{guss}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.37,0:11:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I have a heavy metal mood!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.72,0:11:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,With a bulldozer{/harsh/unstoppable} beat, \NI'll stomp you into the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as I said before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No way I'm losing here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.31,0:11:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The match starts in 3 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.10,0:11:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Be noted, today's rules are: \N200 as initial capital{on hands}, 5000 as the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.92,0:11:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,5000 as the goal? \NIsn't it supposed to be a 2-hour fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.50,0:11:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait for you, however long.{/make sure to wait for you long enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.94,0:12:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever. \NI just have to get this over with as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.35,0:12:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,5 seconds left. \N3, 2, 1. Start.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.89,0:12:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The duration of the Gold Time \Ndepends strictly on player's luck each time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.89,0:12:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean there's no telling when it ends?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.26,0:12:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If it goes on forever, won't it pile up enough \Nto let a player score 5000 with one hit?{guess, no clue how this shit works and what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.85,0:12:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, if it ends with one game, \Nit would cause a huge shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.16,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi pulled a Big already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.82,0:12:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Go for it, hit Big!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.23,0:12:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Show us the power of Gold Time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,While it's still on.{guess, lit: if you want to become younger, my guess is "while the [gold time] iss still young}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.54,0:12:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gold Time lottery has a high chance of 50%{1/2} to activate\Nat the moment of completing a Big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.90,0:12:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's just one in two times \Nand you never know whether you draw it or not.{guess, lit: I'd say one out of every two times, they'll pull one or the other}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.96,0:12:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you draw it, \Nit may decide the match's outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.50,0:12:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you {\i1}have{\i0} to complete the big.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.69,0:13:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Big's conclusion. \NCome here, my Gold Time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.30,0:13:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! Gold Time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.59,0:13:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I acted a bit too overbearing{/pushy/coercive} on him. Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.38,0:13:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So soon...{no way}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.43,0:13:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! \NA Big is on the way{guess}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.79,0:13:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lessgo, lessgo! \NTime to outsrip him{guess} in a blink of an eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.05,0:13:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The two that cannot concert their opinions \Ncan never play a good concert.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.99,0:13:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he playing a concert \Nin duet with machine?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.21,0:13:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.63,0:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This way we'll stomp him at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.17,0:14:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know how to put it. To tell him \N"I'm returning to countryside" and be done with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.87,0:14:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken's Gold Time bonus is still active.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, \Nthe Gold Time is astonishing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it makes the confrontation so much hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold Time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.65,0:14:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice, nice! This is the tables-turning tune! \NKeep this up and we're in the money!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.48,0:14:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well he said he might arrive a little late, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.68,0:15:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped. \NI guess I'll just wait and see until 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ken is having a Renchan{/series} of Gold Time at this point!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.26,0:15:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, \Nhe's going to get miles ahead.{/at this rate, he is way ahead of where he's supposed to be/of himself/Lit: I can't see the future - no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.23,0:15:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No way. At this rate, I'm never winning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Every fight you engage in from now on \Nis a challenge to the dream.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.48,0:15:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So fight with your everything on the line!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.54,0:15:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.21,0:15:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you are to lose in a place like this, \Nthe dream of challenging Daiba Ryo will remain a dream!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Believe! \NYou are still to become so much stronger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.09,0:15:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Not giving up until the very end.\NFighting while putting my everything on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.26,0:15:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I ain't giving up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nailed it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.44,0:15:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's way too late now! \NThe Goddess of Victory favored me already!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.03,0:15:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Big's conclusion... \NCome, Gold Time{this feels like a reference even though it is in fact not, and though I would have preferred to reference jojo or at least shaman kind, neither of them has this sort of catchphrase aside from I choose you which is too stupid}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.55,0:16:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi entered the Gold Time too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.62,0:16:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.28,0:16:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.32,0:16:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a sight to behold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.23,0:16:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To reduce a gap between us{guess, sa is not exactly gap but difference, deepl suggests height or width but that makes even less sense}, \NI have to make sure to collect every multiplier{with certainty}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.40,0:16:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming each game won adds 10 to the score, \NI have to play 100 games to score a 1000 more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.15,0:16:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no telling \Nif I manage to keep up with that timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.22,0:16:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Scheming to catch up with me by raising the speed? \NVery well, let's race{guess}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.02,0:16:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad for you! \NI'm almost at the goal{I hope it's goal, maybe "I'll be in gold very soon}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.19,0:16:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.16,0:16:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Both trying to squeeze dry{guess - chouda} their Gold Times!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not giving up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:16:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not giving up until the very end!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.05,0:17:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit... I'm just one game away from the victory! \NLike hell I'm losing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to score just 15 more{guess}. Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.92,0:17:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold time, don't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.28,0:17:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop. Don't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.86,0:17:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.93,0:17:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.03,0:17:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the errands \Nare taking him somewhat long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.80,0:17:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yo! Lady, you alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.44,0:18:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How about we go pass a glass or two?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.77,0:18:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.95,0:18:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You were waiting for someone?{Lit: Awaited person is coming}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it, move it. \NThere's another one.{absolute guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.70,0:18:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you we should approach her first.{almost an absolute guess as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.52,0:18:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well you never shut up about girls!{same}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.59,0:18:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll wait and see \Nfor just another 30 minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.66,0:18:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:18:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just 10 minutes more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.98,0:19:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to talk this over today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.38,0:19:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Just today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.95,0:19:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy sure was playing on a razor's edge today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.65,0:19:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really saying he is just lucky?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.49,0:19:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Luck is also a part of skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.46,0:19:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi Ginya, \Nhere's to your overwhelming luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.38,0:20:10.35,Song,,0,0,0,,Otonashi Ginya is such a stupid ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.90,0:20:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.10,0:20:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to wait{ for you} long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.66,0:20:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi Ginya \Nis such a stupid ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.91,0:20:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, lady? \NYou ridin'? You not ridin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.38,0:20:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, what time is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.49,0:20:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,11:59.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.49,0:20:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He came!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.30,0:22:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.06,0:22:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.11,0:22:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.50,0:22:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.47,0:22:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.62,0:22:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Believing in Ginya.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.04,0:22:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.65,0:22:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My finger will stop the time.
